  "additional_info": "<b>*</b>On macOS, you need to set the <b>General</b> > <b>Show scroll bars setting</b> in <b>System Preferences</b> to \"<b>Always</b>\" for this property to have any effect.\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<br>\r\n<hr>\r\n<b>For version 63 only<b>: \r\n\r\nthis feature is behind the:\r\n\r\n<ul><li><code>layout.css.scrollbar-colors.enabled</code> \r\n<li><code>layout.css.scrollbar-width.enabled</code> </ul>\r\n\r\npreference (needs to be set to true). To change preferences in Firefox, visit <u>about:config</u>.",
  "style_tags": [],
  "css": "@-moz-document regexp(\"^(https?|moz-extension|ftp)\\:\\/\\/.*$\") {\r\n\r\n    :root {\r\n        scrollbar-face-color: /*[[face-color]]*/ !important; \r\n        scrollbar-track-color: /*[[track-color]]*/ !important; \r\n  \r\n        scrollbar-color: /*[[face-color]]*/ /*[[track-color]]*/ !important;\r\n  \r\n        scrollbar-width: /*[[s-width]]*/ !important;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    select:not([multiple]), select:not([size]) {\r\n       scrollbar-width: auto !important;\r\n    }\r\n\r\n     /*[[inherit]]*/\r\n\r\n}",
